      "date": "2014-03-28 16:00:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nRunning my reproducer with this patch on the client, I'm still seeing two problems: \nnull pointer dereference in cl_object_top\nfile corruption for files in the directory where the reproducer is executed\n\nRun the reproducer and then ls and you get the null pointer dereference.  After rebooting and remounting, lsing in the directory where you executed the test case shows many files have 0 size (and no contents).\n\nI tried to gather a dump of that with debug=-1, but I'm now hitting a GPF in the debug code instead:\n<4> [<ffffffff8128c856>] ? vsnprintf+0x336/0x5e0\n<4> [<ffffffffa030227b>] ? cfs_set_ptldebug_header+0x2b/0xc0 [libcfs]\n<4> [<ffffffffa0312c7a>] libcfs_debug_vmsg2+0x2ea/0xbb0 [libcfs]\n<4> [<ffffffff8128c856>] ? vsnprintf+0x336/0x5e0\n<4> [<ffffffffa0313581>] libcfs_debug_msg+0x41/0x50 [libcfs]\n<4> [<ffffffffa0a2625c>] ll_do_fiemap+0x13c/0x680 [lustre]\n<4> [<ffffffffa0a32934>] ll_fiemap+0x104/0x580 [lustre]\n<4> [<ffffffff8119e1b5>] do_vfs_ioctl+0x505/0x580\n<4> [<ffffffff8119e2b1>] sys_ioctl+0x81/0xa0\n<4> [<ffffffff810e1e4e>] ? __audit_syscall_exit+0x25e/0x290\n<4> [<ffffffff8100b072>] system_call_fastpath+0x16/0x1b\n\nI'm currently uploading a full dump here:\nftp.whamcloud.com/uploads/LU-4619/LU-4619_debug_do_fiemap_gpf.tar.gz\n\nIt should be uploaded by the time you read this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
